I have got a strange issue for query with "or" method. There is a snippet in my query chain as follows:
`realmQuery.beginGroup();
                for (int i = 0; i < folders.size(); i++) {
                    EdoFolder folder = folders.get(i);
                    realmQuery.equalTo("folderId", folder.pId);
                    if (i < folders.size() - 1) {
                        realmQuery.or();
                    }
                }
 realmQuery.endGroup();`
Result: query nothing!  And still nothing even if I change ` folders.size()` to `2`

change it to:
`List<String> folderIds = ArrayUtil.mapNotNull(folders, f -> f.pId);
  realmQuery.in("folderId", folderIds.toArray(new String[0]));`
Result:still nothing!

But, I can get correct results by one of the following ways:
1.  remove the snippet from chain
2. change it to: 
`realmQuery.equalTo("folderId",folders.get(0).pId);` 
OR `realmQuery.equalTo("folderId",folders.get(1).pId);` 
... 
OR `realmQuery.equalTo("folderId",folders.get(folders.size()-1).pId);`
3. change it to: 
`realmQuery.beginGroup();
                for (int i = 0; i < 1; i++) {
                    EdoFolder folder = folders.get(i);
                    realmQuery.equalTo("folderId", folder.pId);
                }
                realmQuery.endGroup();`

In a word, my folderIds are correct, but result is always empty when I query in more than one folderId!

