#### Code Sample

The SyncAdapter is running in a separated process, like the rest of the library. The trip which should be updated may have it's `start_address_name` updated with `null`. Also the field could be `null` already.

DataBase:

 java
static void storeTrip(@NonNull Trip trip) {
        Realm realm = Realm.getInstance(MyApp.getRealmConfig());
        realm.beginTransaction();

        // Make it storable (convert some fields to byte[]).
        trip.makeStorable();

        // Check if trip exists locally.
        Trip localTrip = realm.where(Trip.class)
                .equalTo(Trip.REMOTE_ID, trip.getRemoteId())
                .findFirst();

        // If trip does not exist, create it locally.
        if (localTrip == null) {
            // Generate a new local ID.
            trip.setLocalId(UUID.randomUUID().toString().toUpperCase());
            trip.setFinished(true);

            // Copy the trip to Realm.
            realm.copyToRealm(trip);

        } else {
            // Keep the local ID.
            trip.setLocalId(localTrip.getLocalId());

            // Update the trip in Realm.
            realm.copyToRealmOrUpdate(trip);

        }
        // Here's the crash:
        realm.commitTransaction();
        realm.close();
    }


