> **Questions**: 
**How to persist previously saved Realm data even after an Exception occurs in the application**


#### Goal

If the application already has some realm data saved previously, then this data should persist after an exception has occurred in the application

#### Expected Results

> 1. Save data locally using Realm ex userSelectedValue="abc" is the data which has been saved initially
>2. The app crashed unexpectedly during the flow due to some reason.
>3. When I restart the app, the value of userSelectedValue should persist and not become null

#### Actual Results

>  When I restart the app after a crash, the value of userSelectedValue becomes null

#### Steps & Code to Reproduce

#### Code Sample
>1.  Dto used to store data
`
import io.realm.RealmObject;
import io.realm.annotations.PrimaryKey;

public class RealmLocalObject extends RealmObject {

    @PrimaryKey
    private int userID;
    private String userName;
    private String userLocality;
    private String userGender;


