On Model Generic Class:

    public static <T extends RealmObject> T create(T object) {
        Realm realm = Realm.getDefaultInstance();
        realm.beginTransaction();
        object = realm.copyToRealmOrUpdate(object);
        realm.commitTransaction();
        realm.close();

        return object;
    }

3 - to save the object on updates I do the following code:

    public void save() {
        if (valuesToUpdate.isEmpty())
            return;

        Realm realm = Realm.getDefaultInstance();
        realm.executeTransaction(new Realm.Transaction() {
            @Override
            public void execute(Realm realm) {
                doSave(model);
            }
        });
    }

4 - To send the object I call a method that is async sending the UUID to the job, with that I can fetch the realm object there, this way:

    public T find(String key, Object objId) {
        Realm realm = null;
        T realmObject = null;

        if (objId != null) {
            try {
                realm = Realm.getDefaultInstance();
                realmObject = realm.where(type).equalTo(key, (String) objId).findFirst();
            } catch (Exception ex) {
                Utils.logException(getClass().getSimpleName() + ":find:" + objId, ex);
            } finally {
                if (realm != null) {
                    realm.close();
                }
            }
        }

        this.model = realmObject;
        return realmObject;
    }

